1. Casimir scaling:  
   σ_adj/σ_fund = C₂(adj)/C₂(fund).  

2. Given C₂(adj)=N.  

3. Compute C₂(fund):
   ∑ₐ(T_F^aT_F^a)_{ik} = ∑ₐ(T_F^a)_{ij}(T_F^a)_{jk}
   = ½(δ_{ik}δ_{jj} − (1/N)δ_{ij}δ_{jk})
   = ½(N − 1/N)δ_{ik}
   = (N² − 1)/(2N) δ_{ik}.
   Thus C₂(fund) = (N² − 1)/(2N).  

4. Ratio:
   $$\frac{σ_{\text{adj}}}{σ_{\text{fund}}}
     = \frac{N}{(N²−1)/(2N)}
     = \frac{2N²}{N²−1}\,. $$
